setObjectName: Assigns a unique ID (HlavniPozadi) to the widget, used as a selector for the CSS-style coloring.

QMenu: Creates a dropdown menu containing color options (Red, Blue, Green, Gray).

addAction with lambda: Connects each menu item to the zmen_barvu function, passing a specific color code as an argument.

setMenu: Attaches the created menu to the btn_menu button.

self.zmen_barvu("gray"): Sets the default background color to gray when the application starts.

Methods (Logic)
zmen_barvu:

Enables background styling for the widget.

Applies a StyleSheet (CSS) that dynamically changes the window background and sets fixed styles
for all QLineEdit (large bold text) and QPushButton (rounded corners and semi-transparent white background) elements.


